1
00:00:15,882 --> 00:00:17,760
Hey, can I give you
a hand with that?

2
00:00:17,784 --> 00:00:19,329
Oh, thanks, John.

3
00:00:19,353 --> 00:00:22,065
Paid a fortune for it and
the damn thing's stuck.

4
00:00:22,089 --> 00:00:24,334
No problem, as long as I
can sneak under a corner of it.

5
00:00:24,358 --> 00:00:26,469
I left mine at the
house on my way out.

6
00:00:26,493 --> 00:00:28,738
Ooh, I hate coming in
to work in the morning

7
00:00:28,762 --> 00:00:29,872
when it's still dark.

8
00:00:31,632 --> 00:00:33,493
That doesn't look promising.

9
00:00:33,517 --> 00:00:37,530
Yeah, perfect start to what's
bound to be a perfect day!

10
00:00:37,554 --> 00:00:39,332
We got a 93-year-old
woman with COPD.

11
00:00:39,356 --> 00:00:41,301
Increased wheezing
due to smoke inhalation,

12
00:00:41,325 --> 00:00:42,768
with no evidence
of facial burns.

13
00:00:42,792 --> 00:00:44,737
BP's 134 over 92, pulse 96.

14
00:00:44,761 --> 00:00:47,140
Give her five albuterol,
get her on a pulse ox,

15
00:00:47,164 --> 00:00:48,274
and order chest films.

16
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:49,342
What's going on?

17
00:00:49,366 --> 00:00:51,077
Oh, there was a fire
in a nursing home.

18
00:00:51,101 --> 00:00:53,179
There weren't enough
people there to get 'em out.

19
00:00:53,203 --> 00:00:54,965
Carter, can you get
this last ambulance?

20
00:00:54,989 --> 00:00:57,667
MAN 1:90-year-old with
tachypnea and altered mental status.

21
00:00:57,691 --> 00:00:58,768
BP's 95 over 60.

22
00:00:58,792 --> 00:01:00,136
No singed nasal hairs.

23
00:01:00,160 --> 00:01:02,322
They're sending us
two more, one critical.

24
00:01:02,346 --> 00:01:04,557
Full thickness burns.
Who's on the desk?

25
00:01:04,581 --> 00:01:06,826
Nobody. Steve's sick,
and Randi left at 6:30.

26
00:01:06,850 --> 00:01:08,645
She didn't wait for
her replacement?

27
00:01:08,669 --> 00:01:09,879
I am not her keeper.

28
00:01:09,903 --> 00:01:11,280
If you wanna
bitch, bitch at her.

29
00:01:11,304 --> 00:01:12,782
Haleh, I need you.

30
00:01:12,806 --> 00:01:14,383
Oh, and Jeanie called.

31
00:01:14,407 --> 00:01:16,727
She's not coming
in today either.

32
00:01:18,596 --> 00:01:21,474
Got basketball practice, or
are you coming straight home?

33
00:01:21,498 --> 00:01:23,443
- I have practice.
- You ready?

34
00:01:23,467 --> 00:01:24,711
Yeah.

35
00:01:24,735 --> 00:01:25,879
Good morning. Morning.

36
00:01:25,903 --> 00:01:27,280
Where's your backpack?

37
00:01:27,304 --> 00:01:28,465
Mm-hm.

38
00:01:28,489 --> 00:01:29,766
It's in the upstairs bathroom

39
00:01:29,790 --> 00:01:31,267
on top of the toilet,
and you dumped

40
00:01:31,291 --> 00:01:33,235
your basketball stuff
on the basement steps.

41
00:01:33,259 --> 00:01:34,804
If you want it to end
up in the washer,

42
00:01:34,828 --> 00:01:35,872
you put it in the basket.

43
00:01:35,896 --> 00:01:37,439
She can hit a
20-foot fading jumper,

44
00:01:37,463 --> 00:01:39,864
but she can't get within
10 yards of the hamper.

45
00:01:40,734 --> 00:01:42,578
Yeesh.

46
00:01:42,602 --> 00:01:44,468
You got a minute? Not really.

47
00:01:45,739 --> 00:01:47,205
Yeah, uh...

48
00:01:49,943 --> 00:01:52,310
Carla told me that
Reece might not be mine.

49
00:01:54,314 --> 00:01:55,914
What are you gonna do?

50
00:01:57,718 --> 00:01:59,261
I don't know.

51
00:01:59,285 --> 00:02:02,031
I don't know that I believe her,
with everything that's going on.

52
00:02:03,289 --> 00:02:05,568
That bitch. What the
hell is the matter with her?

53
00:02:05,592 --> 00:02:07,537
Jackie. Look... No. No.

54
00:02:07,561 --> 00:02:09,039
Everything she's
put you through,

55
00:02:09,063 --> 00:02:10,343
and she isn't even sure?

56
00:02:13,684 --> 00:02:15,495
I'm sorry.

57
00:02:15,519 --> 00:02:16,930
But I don't know what's worse.

58
00:02:16,954 --> 00:02:18,197
That she's always known,

59
00:02:18,221 --> 00:02:20,581
or she's just doing
this to get Reece?

60
00:02:21,207 --> 00:02:22,485
Well, I got a paternity test.

61
00:02:22,509 --> 00:02:24,454
I, uh... I haven't taken it yet.

62
00:02:24,478 --> 00:02:25,855
How long does it take?

63
00:02:25,879 --> 00:02:27,807
I don't know. I don't
know that I'm gonna do it.

64
00:02:27,831 --> 00:02:29,197
You have to.

65
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:31,783
What if I'm not his father, huh?

66
00:02:33,220 --> 00:02:35,448
What are you gonna do,
wait till he gets older, Peter?

67
00:02:35,472 --> 00:02:37,216
He's bound to find
out. Yeah, I know. I...

68
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:38,517
Yeah, and then he's gonna know

69
00:02:38,541 --> 00:02:40,070
that you've lied to him.

70
00:03:41,805 --> 00:03:43,583
Hi. Hi.

71
00:03:43,607 --> 00:03:44,651
What do you want?

72
00:03:44,675 --> 00:03:45,652
Well, I called,

73
00:03:45,676 --> 00:03:47,654
but the phone just kept ringing.

74
00:03:47,678 --> 00:03:49,456
I don't always hear
it, it's down the hall.

75
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:50,774
I gotta get to work.

76
00:03:50,798 --> 00:03:52,441
Are you still working
at the pharmacy?

77
00:03:52,465 --> 00:03:54,577
Yeah. Pay sucks, but
the hours are good.

78
00:03:54,601 --> 00:03:56,880
Well, look, your tests
came back after you left.

79
00:03:56,904 --> 00:03:58,381
You gotta come
back to the hospital

80
00:03:58,405 --> 00:04:01,017
and get treated for
the bladder infection.

81
00:04:01,041 --> 00:04:02,819
A bladder infection
can be very dangerous

82
00:04:02,843 --> 00:04:04,154
when you're pregnant.

83
00:04:04,178 --> 00:04:05,688
I'll come by as soon as I can.

84
00:04:05,712 --> 00:04:07,223
Have you given any more thought

85
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:09,025
to the detox program?

86
00:04:09,049 --> 00:04:10,726
You know, you really have to.

87
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:13,863
Yeah, I stopped using
about, uh, five days ago.

88
00:04:13,887 --> 00:04:14,864
Oh, good for you.

89
00:04:14,888 --> 00:04:16,021
Yeah, thanks again.

90
00:04:18,459 --> 00:04:21,003
Yeah, I don't give a damn
how many patients you've got.

91
00:04:21,027 --> 00:04:22,672
Excuse me. Hey, you know what?

92
00:04:22,696 --> 00:04:23,840
We are drowning here,

93
00:04:23,864 --> 00:04:26,275
and I need some
qualified bodies.

94
00:04:26,299 --> 00:04:29,211
Excuse me, I'm, uh... Go away.

95
00:04:29,235 --> 00:04:32,181
I've got 11 fried old folks, you
wanna compare patient loads?

96
00:04:32,205 --> 00:04:34,317
Uh-uh. You need something,
talk to the boss lady.

97
00:04:34,341 --> 00:04:36,202
Hey, you're in a
nasty car accident,

98
00:04:36,226 --> 00:04:39,438
I hope you end up down
here, so that I can personally be

99
00:04:39,462 --> 00:04:42,229
of absolutely no damn
help to you whatsoever!

100
00:04:43,350 --> 00:04:44,961
Twerp. Excuse me.

101
00:04:44,985 --> 00:04:46,963
Hi. Uh, I'm Andrew...

102
00:04:46,987 --> 00:04:49,015
Do you have an M.D.
behind your name?

103
00:04:49,039 --> 00:04:50,583
No, I... Okay, then have a seat.

104
00:04:50,607 --> 00:04:51,607
I'll get to you later.

105
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:56,055
Uh, Margaret Ramey sent me.

106
00:04:56,079 --> 00:04:57,424
You're a desk clerk?

107
00:04:57,448 --> 00:04:58,558
Yes, ma'am.

108
00:04:58,582 --> 00:05:01,016
Good. Then get back
here now. Come on.

109
00:05:03,686 --> 00:05:04,830
Okay, so you want me to...

110
00:05:04,854 --> 00:05:07,867
You're a clerk. Clerk.
Malik, get on the phone

111
00:05:07,891 --> 00:05:09,168
to anybody who has the day off.

112
00:05:09,192 --> 00:05:10,536
Tell them to get into work today

113
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:12,605
if they still wanna
work here tomorrow.

114
00:05:12,629 --> 00:05:14,607
Oh, God! Can I help you, ma'am?

115
00:05:14,631 --> 00:05:17,110
Oh, I... I've lost my husband.

116
00:05:17,134 --> 00:05:18,111
Were you in the fire?

117
00:05:18,135 --> 00:05:20,279
Barry's my husband's name

118
00:05:20,303 --> 00:05:22,315
and I was following
him down the hall,

119
00:05:22,339 --> 00:05:24,617
and they went so fast.

120
00:05:24,641 --> 00:05:26,885
Uh-huh. Your husband's
name is Barry? Yes.

121
00:05:26,909 --> 00:05:28,754
Well, let's go see if
we can find him for you.

122
00:05:28,778 --> 00:05:30,156
Oh, why, thank you.

123
00:05:30,180 --> 00:05:32,492
Sir, can you take a
deep breath for me?

124
00:05:32,516 --> 00:05:34,059
Pulse ox 82 on four liters.

125
00:05:34,083 --> 00:05:35,662
Hey, I just found
your patient's wife

126
00:05:35,686 --> 00:05:36,829
wandering in the hall.

127
00:05:36,853 --> 00:05:38,631
Can I bring her in?
Absolutely. You free?

128
00:05:38,655 --> 00:05:41,233
Yeah, I was just heading back
to the desk to grab another one.

129
00:05:41,257 --> 00:05:43,035
Well, I got two. You
can have this one.

130
00:05:43,059 --> 00:05:44,671
No singed nasal hairs.

131
00:05:44,695 --> 00:05:46,523
Barry, I'm right here.

132
00:05:46,547 --> 00:05:49,392
Sir, I need you to lean forward
so I can listen to your back.

133
00:05:49,416 --> 00:05:52,767
- He can't lift himself.
- I...

134
00:05:55,305 --> 00:05:56,816
Wet crackles bilaterally.

135
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:58,951
Put him on a
non-rebreather mask.

136
00:05:58,975 --> 00:06:01,004
MS, CHF, coronary
artery disease.

137
00:06:01,028 --> 00:06:02,989
All right, S4 gallop.
Let's get a nitro drip.

138
00:06:03,013 --> 00:06:05,375
Titrate to a systolic of 100.

139
00:06:05,399 --> 00:06:08,495
Add another 80 of Lasix,
and four of morphine.

140
00:06:08,519 --> 00:06:10,679
You got it? Yeah. Yeah.

141
00:06:12,406 --> 00:06:14,617
78-year-old woman
with rheumatoid arthritis.

142
00:06:14,641 --> 00:06:17,620
Contusion to the right thigh.
BP's 155 over 88, pulse 96.

143
00:06:17,644 --> 00:06:20,089
Three-centimeter vertical
laceration to the forehead.

144
00:06:20,113 --> 00:06:22,358
Knew I should've had
that third cup of coffee.

145
00:06:22,382 --> 00:06:23,560
What's going on?

146
00:06:23,584 --> 00:06:25,628
Nursing-home fire.
Gabe, check the residents.

147
00:06:25,652 --> 00:06:27,230
Make sure all the
majors are covered.

148
00:06:27,254 --> 00:06:28,898
And, Carol, can you
take over the desk?

149
00:06:28,922 --> 00:06:30,984
They're stacking
up like cordwood.

150
00:06:31,008 --> 00:06:32,785
No physical sign of
the smoke inhalation,

151
00:06:32,809 --> 00:06:34,687
but she's still short
of breath and hypoxic.

152
00:06:34,711 --> 00:06:35,821
Pulse ox is down to 84.

153
00:06:35,845 --> 00:06:37,056
Uh-huh. Crank her up to 10.

154
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:38,424
All right?

155
00:06:38,448 --> 00:06:40,759
What the hell's going on?
Her chest is clear. I mean...

156
00:06:40,783 --> 00:06:42,028
You wanna get Dr. Greene?

157
00:06:42,052 --> 00:06:44,414
Uh, no. What's her temp?

158
00:06:44,438 --> 00:06:46,003
101.2.

159
00:06:47,206 --> 00:06:49,035
Will you appreciate
the coarse rhonchi

160
00:06:49,059 --> 00:06:50,725
at the right base?

161
00:06:55,832 --> 00:06:57,043
She's got pneumonia.

162
00:06:57,067 --> 00:06:59,128
Not much gets by
you, does it, Dr. Dave?

163
00:06:59,152 --> 00:07:00,696
CBC, blood cultures...

164
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:03,160
Chest x-ray, ceftriaxone. Sign.

165
00:07:04,541 --> 00:07:06,185
You know, uh,
Andy does imitations.

166
00:07:06,209 --> 00:07:07,387
Ask him.

167
00:07:07,411 --> 00:07:08,787
Imitations, huh?

168
00:07:08,811 --> 00:07:10,890
Oh, I'm better at improv.
You know, Second City.

169
00:07:10,914 --> 00:07:12,025
This is just my day job.

170
00:07:12,049 --> 00:07:13,426
Yo, man, do Keanu Reeves, man.

171
00:07:13,450 --> 00:07:15,228
No. Aw, come on. Do something.

172
00:07:15,252 --> 00:07:17,730
Go ahead.

173
00:07:17,754 --> 00:07:20,366
Whoa! So you're a
little pregnant, huh?

174
00:07:20,390 --> 00:07:22,201
All right.

175
00:07:22,225 --> 00:07:24,070
You picked a name
for the little dude yet?

176
00:07:24,094 --> 00:07:25,338
No. No, I haven't.

177
00:07:25,362 --> 00:07:28,663
Well, how 'bout Leif?
Or Bodhi? Or Keanu?

178
00:07:29,799 --> 00:07:32,211
Keanu is a most excellent name.

179
00:07:32,235 --> 00:07:33,712
That's very good.

180
00:07:33,736 --> 00:07:35,515
Malik, did you get ahold Jeanie?

181
00:07:35,539 --> 00:07:37,216
Yeah, she says she
couldn't make it in.

182
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:39,252
She hasn't made it in
all week. Call her again.

183
00:07:39,276 --> 00:07:40,719
Tell her to come in here.

184
00:07:40,743 --> 00:07:43,895
If not to work, then to explain
to me why I shouldn't fire her.

185
00:07:45,231 --> 00:07:47,276
Just had a great
pickup. Oh, yeah?

186
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,778
Elderly woman
who was in that fire,

187
00:07:48,802 --> 00:07:51,347
presented with rapid breathing
and altered mental status.

188
00:07:51,371 --> 00:07:52,882
Tachypneic and hypoxic.

189
00:07:52,906 --> 00:07:54,750
You're figuring smoke
inhalation, right?

190
00:07:54,774 --> 00:07:56,118
Your Bunsen burner's still on.

191
00:07:56,142 --> 00:07:57,720
That one sticks,
you gotta jiggle it.

192
00:07:57,744 --> 00:07:58,921
Pulse ox was 84. You with me?

193
00:07:58,945 --> 00:08:00,756
Struggling, but I
think I get the picture.

194
00:08:00,780 --> 00:08:02,758
I was tempted to just
write it up as inhalation,

195
00:08:02,782 --> 00:08:04,727
but I noticed a few
subtle physical findings.

196
00:08:04,751 --> 00:08:06,496
Quiet crackles in
the right middle lobe,

197
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:08,163
a slight dullness to percussion,

198
00:08:08,187 --> 00:08:09,331
and a low-grade fever.

199
00:08:09,355 --> 00:08:10,933
Pneumonia.

200
00:08:10,957 --> 00:08:12,802
Right.

201
00:08:12,826 --> 00:08:15,170
I figure I'm gonna find
some gram-positive diplococci

202
00:08:15,194 --> 00:08:16,338
in her sputum.

203
00:08:16,362 --> 00:08:18,107
She's lucky she had
you as her physician.

204
00:08:18,131 --> 00:08:19,575
Damn straight.

205
00:08:19,599 --> 00:08:22,078
Haleh told me she heard
the rhonchi on the patient

206
00:08:22,102 --> 00:08:23,382
and told you.

207
00:08:28,992 --> 00:08:31,504
I... I can't understand
what he's saying.

208
00:08:31,528 --> 00:08:33,239
He's not getting enough oxygen.

209
00:08:33,263 --> 00:08:36,059
It can lead to confusion
and disorientation.

210
00:08:36,083 --> 00:08:38,294
His lungs are very sick.

211
00:08:38,318 --> 00:08:39,612
Right now our only option

212
00:08:39,636 --> 00:08:41,680
is to place a tube
down his throat

213
00:08:41,704 --> 00:08:42,949
to help him breathe.

214
00:08:42,973 --> 00:08:45,584
But I don't know that
that will be helpful.

215
00:08:45,608 --> 00:08:48,108
Well, is there a chance
he can get better?

216
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:53,609
There is a chance. But
in his declining health...

217
00:08:53,633 --> 00:08:55,244
I'm not optimistic.

218
00:08:55,268 --> 00:08:56,467
But he could get better?

219
00:08:58,304 --> 00:08:59,304
Yes, he could.

220
00:09:02,008 --> 00:09:03,391
Then let's try it.

221
00:09:04,894 --> 00:09:06,744
It could also be his heart.

222
00:09:10,166 --> 00:09:12,311
Why don't we run some
more tests, and, um...

223
00:09:12,335 --> 00:09:15,603
Just make sure that we're
doing the right thing first.

224
00:09:17,207 --> 00:09:19,185
Lily, can we get
Cardiology down here?

225
00:09:19,209 --> 00:09:21,187
To, uh, do an echo?

226
00:09:21,211 --> 00:09:22,376
Yeah.

227
00:09:27,784 --> 00:09:28,827
Help me!

228
00:09:28,851 --> 00:09:29,895
How you doing?

229
00:09:29,919 --> 00:09:33,032
Uh, 89-year-old woman.
Agitated, delusional.

230
00:09:33,056 --> 00:09:35,434
Vitals normal. No signs of
smoke inhalation or injury.

231
00:09:35,458 --> 00:09:37,069
What have you done so far?

232
00:09:37,093 --> 00:09:38,621
Gave five of
Haldol, two of Ativan.

233
00:09:38,645 --> 00:09:40,523
I lost my reading
glasses on the way in.

234
00:09:40,547 --> 00:09:41,507
Help me!

235
00:09:41,531 --> 00:09:42,875
Why won't you help me?

236
00:09:42,899 --> 00:09:43,876
Please!

237
00:09:43,900 --> 00:09:45,094
Help me!

238
00:09:45,118 --> 00:09:46,929
These dementia cases are so sad.

239
00:09:46,953 --> 00:09:49,364
Hated my Geriatrics rotation.
One reason I chose Pedes.

240
00:09:49,388 --> 00:09:50,767
Help me! Please! Ma'am.

241
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:52,101
You're doing fine. Help me!

242
00:09:52,125 --> 00:09:55,855
Help me! Help me! Please!

243
00:09:55,879 --> 00:09:58,163
Help me! Please! Please.

244
00:09:59,082 --> 00:10:00,998
Help me, help me.

245
00:10:01,952 --> 00:10:04,396
How's she doing? Fine.

246
00:10:04,420 --> 00:10:05,531
Excuse me.

247
00:10:07,691 --> 00:10:09,168
Think we're
getting on top of it.

248
00:10:09,192 --> 00:10:10,836
Three have been
admitted to Medicine.

249
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:12,538
The broken hip
went up to surgery.

250
00:10:12,562 --> 00:10:13,639
One's in CICU,

251
00:10:13,663 --> 00:10:16,241
and five were
treated and released.

252
00:10:16,265 --> 00:10:17,910
You smell gas? Yes, I do.

253
00:10:17,934 --> 00:10:18,945
Malik, smell that?

254
00:10:18,969 --> 00:10:19,946
Yeah.

255
00:10:19,970 --> 00:10:21,480
Okay, I'll call Maintenance.

256
