and give the baby a chance.

772
00:33:18,330 --> 00:33:19,674
Wanna talk about it?

773
00:33:19,698 --> 00:33:22,193
We could drown our sorrows
in a couple of ginger ales.

774
00:33:22,217 --> 00:33:23,561
No, thanks,

775
00:33:23,585 --> 00:33:25,747
the girls are throwing me
a surprise baby shower.

776
00:33:25,771 --> 00:33:27,949
I thought that was
supposed to be a surprise.

777
00:33:27,973 --> 00:33:29,756
I'll look surprised.

778
00:33:37,032 --> 00:33:38,497
I miss Doug.

779
00:33:40,785 --> 00:33:41,785
You call him?

780
00:33:44,723 --> 00:33:47,201
Has he called you?

781
00:33:47,225 --> 00:33:50,070
He leaves messages
on my machine.

782
00:33:50,094 --> 00:33:52,607
I think he calls when
he knows I won't be there

783
00:33:52,631 --> 00:33:55,109
so I don't have to talk
to him if I don't want to.

784
00:33:55,133 --> 00:33:56,616
You don't want to?

785
00:33:59,187 --> 00:34:01,232
I don't know what
else there is to say.

786
00:34:05,227 --> 00:34:06,988
Rain check on that ginger ale?

787
00:34:07,012 --> 00:34:08,177
Sure.

788
00:34:26,247 --> 00:34:27,692
Hey, Malik. Yeah.

789
00:34:27,716 --> 00:34:30,127
Have you seen the T-sheet
on the Bernero kid's chart?

790
00:34:30,151 --> 00:34:31,629
The diabetes kid?
Why is it so hard

791
00:34:31,653 --> 00:34:34,065
to keep them on the charts?
It was there a while ago.

792
00:34:34,089 --> 00:34:36,434
Yeah, I hate this. Now I
gotta fill out a whole new chart.

793
00:34:36,458 --> 00:34:37,936
I don't have time for this crap.

794
00:34:37,960 --> 00:34:41,172
Randi, Bernero kid in
Curtain 3 can go home.

795
00:34:41,196 --> 00:34:44,241
Just a little case
of the stomach flu.

796
00:34:44,265 --> 00:34:46,705
Kick him out of there.
We need the bed.

797
00:34:52,074 --> 00:34:53,251
Randi, have you seen Kerry?

798
00:34:53,275 --> 00:34:54,885
Um, Curtain 2.

799
00:34:54,909 --> 00:34:56,020
Thanks.

800
00:34:56,044 --> 00:34:57,221
Hey. Hi.

801
00:34:57,245 --> 00:34:58,722
How's the baby?
He's doin' great.

802
00:34:58,746 --> 00:35:01,492
We're having a shower for
Carol. You ought to stop by.

803
00:35:01,516 --> 00:35:03,916
Yeah, I'll try. All right.

804
00:35:05,420 --> 00:35:08,299
Okay, hang a banana bag
and try to dress those abrasions.

805
00:35:08,323 --> 00:35:09,700
I think he fell on
his face again.

806
00:35:09,724 --> 00:35:12,220
Kerry, Malik called, said
it was important I come in?

807
00:35:12,244 --> 00:35:14,722
Yeah. You know, I
checked your timecards

808
00:35:14,746 --> 00:35:16,924
and you've worked two
days in the last three weeks.

809
00:35:16,948 --> 00:35:18,025
We depend on you down here.

810
00:35:18,049 --> 00:35:19,694
And when you call
in at the last minute,

811
00:35:19,718 --> 00:35:21,529
it just makes it tough
on everybody else.

812
00:35:21,553 --> 00:35:24,065
I'm not coming back.

813
00:35:24,089 --> 00:35:26,500
I'm sorry, I didn't mean to
make it tough on everybody.

814
00:35:26,524 --> 00:35:29,737
I didn't intend to. I should've
come to talk to you earlier.

815
00:35:29,761 --> 00:35:31,489
Well, is everything all right?

816
00:35:31,513 --> 00:35:33,557
I've never been happier.

817
00:35:33,581 --> 00:35:35,526
I have Reggie and the baby.

818
00:35:35,550 --> 00:35:38,296
And every time I'm at work,
I want to be home with them.

819
00:35:38,320 --> 00:35:40,048
That's great. So...

820
00:35:40,072 --> 00:35:42,300
if you need me to
work a few shifts... No.

821
00:35:42,324 --> 00:35:43,934
No, no, no.

822
00:35:43,958 --> 00:35:47,171
But as the baby gets older
and doesn't need you so much,

823
00:35:47,195 --> 00:35:50,474
call me. There will always
be a job for you here.

824
00:35:50,498 --> 00:35:52,114
Thanks, Kerry.

825
00:35:53,101 --> 00:35:54,429
I'm gonna miss you.

826
00:35:54,453 --> 00:35:56,734
I'm gonna miss you too.

827
00:36:00,358 --> 00:36:01,519
Hey.

828
00:36:01,543 --> 00:36:02,904
Hello, baby.

829
00:36:02,928 --> 00:36:05,706
Oh, Roger was gonna pick
him up at your place later.

830
00:36:05,730 --> 00:36:07,692
Yeah, I know, I know.
Actually, you know what,

831
00:36:07,716 --> 00:36:09,894
I called him and told him I
was going to drop him off.

832
00:36:09,918 --> 00:36:12,113
Roger! ROGER: Yeah?

833
00:36:12,137 --> 00:36:14,082
Reece is here.

834
00:36:14,106 --> 00:36:15,366
Hey, I, um... ROGER: My man.

835
00:36:15,390 --> 00:36:19,191
I got this DNA kit
to test for paternity.

836
00:36:20,077 --> 00:36:21,261
And?

837
00:36:22,497 --> 00:36:24,042
And I'm not gonna use it.

838
00:36:24,066 --> 00:36:26,844
I'm gonna throw it away.

839
00:36:26,868 --> 00:36:28,096
Why?

840
00:36:28,120 --> 00:36:29,552
Carla...

841
00:36:31,389 --> 00:36:34,224
I put my hand on your stomach
when you were pregnant.

842
00:36:35,527 --> 00:36:37,727
And I felt him move.

843
00:36:40,165 --> 00:36:41,509
I was there when he was born

844
00:36:41,533 --> 00:36:43,933
and all those
nights in the NICU.

845
00:36:45,504 --> 00:36:47,181
I wake up in the
morning, that little boy

846
00:36:47,205 --> 00:36:49,772
is the first thing on my mind.

847
00:36:51,543 --> 00:36:53,877
When I go to sleep
at night, he's the last.

848
00:36:58,082 --> 00:36:59,549
I love him.

849
00:37:00,685 --> 00:37:02,463
He's my son.

850
00:37:02,487 --> 00:37:04,198
I don't care about biology.

851
00:37:04,222 --> 00:37:07,657
I don't need some damn
DNA kit to tell me that.

852
00:37:09,494 --> 00:37:12,873
I don't have a whole
lot in my life, Carla.

853
00:37:12,897 --> 00:37:15,376
My career...

854
00:37:15,400 --> 00:37:18,934
Jackie and her
kids and that boy.

855
00:37:21,039 --> 00:37:24,407
He means more to me than
all the rest of them combined.

856
00:37:26,411 --> 00:37:28,155
I'd lay down in front
of a train for him.

857
00:37:28,179 --> 00:37:31,347
That's how I love him.

858
00:37:32,750 --> 00:37:34,884
So I'm asking. I am...

859
00:37:42,260 --> 00:37:44,060
I'm asking you...

860
00:37:46,631 --> 00:37:48,398
Please...

861
00:37:55,940 --> 00:37:59,409
Don't... Don't... Don't
take my son away from me.

862
00:38:05,584 --> 00:38:06,849
Please.

863
00:38:14,292 --> 00:38:16,336
Carol, Weaver
needs you at the desk.

864
00:38:16,360 --> 00:38:17,572
Something about overtime.

865
00:38:17,596 --> 00:38:18,695
Great. Okay.

866
00:38:19,998 --> 00:38:22,443
Surprise!

867
00:38:22,467 --> 00:38:24,745
Oh, my God!

868
00:38:24,769 --> 00:38:28,315
You guys... You didn't
know? I had no idea.

869
00:38:28,339 --> 00:38:30,951
We chipped in on the bassinets.

870
00:38:30,975 --> 00:38:32,653
We have no money anymore.

871
00:38:32,677 --> 00:38:35,589
Aw, they're beautiful.

872
00:38:35,613 --> 00:38:36,591
Dr. Weaver,

873
00:38:36,615 --> 00:38:38,492
Dr. Lawrence is
down in Trauma 2.

874
00:38:38,516 --> 00:38:40,016
You were looking for him, right?

875
00:38:43,971 --> 00:38:45,605
Where have you been?

876
00:38:47,075 --> 00:38:49,158
Out walking by the lake.

877
00:38:51,329 --> 00:38:52,928
I was worried about you.

878
00:38:55,400 --> 00:38:58,029
<i>When despair for
the world Grows in me</i>

879
00:38:58,053 --> 00:39:00,731
<i>I go and lie down
Where the wood drake</i>

880
00:39:00,755 --> 00:39:04,368
<i>Rests in his beauty On the water</i>

881
00:39:04,392 --> 00:39:06,759
<i>And the great heron feeds.</i>

882
00:39:10,131 --> 00:39:12,743
<i>I come into the
peace Of wild things</i>

883
00:39:12,767 --> 00:39:16,135
<i>Who do not tax their lives
With forethought of grief.</i>

884
00:39:19,024 --> 00:39:21,519
<i>I come into the
presence Of still water</i>

885
00:39:21,543 --> 00:39:25,222
<i>And feel above me
The day-blind stars</i>

886
00:39:25,246 --> 00:39:27,180
<i>Waiting with their light</i>

887
00:39:29,650 --> 00:39:34,520
<i>And for a time, I
rest in the peace</i>

888
00:39:36,424 --> 00:39:39,625
<i>Of the world and am free.</i>

889
00:39:46,701 --> 00:39:49,263
How can I remember
a William Blake poem

890
00:39:49,287 --> 00:39:52,399
I memorized over 30 years ago,

891
00:39:52,423 --> 00:39:55,703
and not remember
that I saw a woman

892
00:39:55,727 --> 00:39:58,377
with a sprained
ankle this afternoon?

893
00:40:05,503 --> 00:40:08,266
I started to notice something
was wrong about a year ago.

894
00:40:08,290 --> 00:40:11,686
You know, memory loss

895
00:40:11,710 --> 00:40:15,311
and not being able
to find the right word.

896
00:40:17,682 --> 00:40:20,594
I went to Boston to see
an old classmate of mine,

897
00:40:20,618 --> 00:40:22,251
a neurologist.

898
00:40:26,124 --> 00:40:27,467
He did a PET scan, and it...

899
00:40:27,491 --> 00:40:29,653
It showed bilateral
hypoperfusion

900
00:40:29,677 --> 00:40:31,677
to the parietal areas.

901
00:40:33,414 --> 00:40:36,160
He started me on Aricept.

902
00:40:36,184 --> 00:40:37,511
It's supposed to...

903
00:40:37,535 --> 00:40:39,279
put the brakes on... On...

904
00:40:39,303 --> 00:40:40,981
On the Alzheimer's.
But I guess...

905
00:40:41,005 --> 00:40:45,970
Guess it, uh... It
didn't help enough.

906
00:40:45,994 --> 00:40:49,373
Roz Chow is doing great work

907
00:40:49,397 --> 00:40:51,842
upstairs at the Comprehensive
Dementia Center.

908
00:40:51,866 --> 00:40:53,227
You should go see her.

909
00:40:53,251 --> 00:40:56,063
What for? I have a
progressive neurologic disorder.

910
00:40:56,087 --> 00:40:59,366
They're working with
neurotrophins and antioxidants.

911
00:40:59,390 --> 00:41:01,652
Maybe you could
get into a clinical trial.

912
00:41:01,676 --> 00:41:03,916
I was thinking of
committing suicide.

913
00:41:07,232 --> 00:41:08,942
I don't...

914
00:41:08,966 --> 00:41:11,567
I can't figure out
the best time to do it.

915
00:41:13,104 --> 00:41:16,950
Too early, and I'll miss
what little life I have left.

916
00:41:16,974 --> 00:41:19,720
If I wait too long, I
won't remember to do it.

917
00:41:22,280 --> 00:41:24,880
Please don't say that.

918
00:41:28,169 --> 00:41:30,903
God, I'm gonna
miss this. You know...

919
00:41:34,042 --> 00:41:37,605
You know, medicine
has been my whole life.

920
00:41:37,629 --> 00:41:41,242
No. No, you could stay on

921
00:41:41,266 --> 00:41:43,377
and you could lecture
the medical students

922
00:41:43,401 --> 00:41:46,146
and the residents.

923
00:41:46,170 --> 00:41:47,937
But not see patients, right?

924
00:41:50,158 --> 00:41:52,603
Gabe, you are a brilliant doctor

925
00:41:52,627 --> 00:41:54,405
and you are a wonderful teacher.

926
00:41:54,429 --> 00:41:55,973
Please...

927
00:41:55,997 --> 00:41:58,197
Please don't give
up those gifts.

928
00:42:02,453 --> 00:42:04,854
Look, I saw a
woman this morning.

929
00:42:08,293 --> 00:42:10,193
Dementia. She had...

930
00:42:12,463 --> 00:42:15,731
She had no idea where she
was. She didn't know who she was.

931
00:42:22,740 --> 00:42:24,874
Ten years, that'll be me.

932
00:42:27,345 --> 00:42:28,845
Bedridden...

933
00:42:30,548 --> 00:42:35,617
in diapers... locked
away in some home...

934
00:42:37,421 --> 00:42:39,488
nobody coming to see me.

935
00:42:42,876 --> 00:42:45,227
I'll come and see you.

936
00:42:49,367 --> 00:42:50,644
Yeah, but I won't...

937
00:42:50,668 --> 00:42:53,402
I won't know you're there.
